      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "PMC_PLACEHOLDER",
      "text_span_id": "results_1",
      "text": "Among 630 participants (mean [SD] age, 59.4 [13.1] years), age-standardized rates of incidence were 1.2 (95% CI: 0.4\u20132.1) per 100, 000.",
      "confidence": 0.95,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "retrospective cohort study",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "PMC_PLACEHOLDER:results:2:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "PMC_PLACEHOLDER",
      "text_span_id": "results_2",
      "text": "All-cause mortality was 50.8 per 1000 person-years (95% CI: 42.4\u201360.4).",
      "confidence": 0.95,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "retrospective cohort study",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "PMC_PLACEHOLDER:results:3:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "PMC_PLACEHOLDER",
      "text_span_id": "results_3",
      "text": "Mongolian had a higher age-standardized 5-year prevalence rate than Han (3.2[95% CI: 2.5\u20134.0] vs 2.3[95% CI: 1.7\u20133.0], P=0.016).",
      "confidence": 0.95,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "retrospective cohort study",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "PMC_PLACEHOLDER:discussion:1:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "PMC_PLACEHOLDER",
      "text_span_id": "discussion_1",
      "text": "BRCA1/2 (e.g. 5296del4 in BRCA1 and 6174delT in BRCA2) mutation was considered as the crucial risk factor in breast cancer, and BRCA2 mutations were more common in MBC.",
